 {"id":"bd-pgs-epic","title":"PORT: pwd/grp/shadow line serializers (putpwent/putgrent/putspent) to core","description":"Lift the format!()-with-from_utf8_unchecked line serialization out of putpwent (glibc_internal_abi.rs:5685, ~40 lines), putgrent (glibc_internal_abi.rs:5619, ~35 lines), and putspent (unistd_abi.rs:13366, ~37 lines) into pure-safe core::{pwd,grp} formatters operating on byte slices. Each writes one colon-separated record terminated with newline. The C-ABI marshalling — *const libc::passwd/group/spwd field reads, fwrite at the boundary — stays at the boundary.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T09:33:20.372874Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T09:37:21.475889Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T09:37:21.475889Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~110 lines of from_utf8_unchecked + format!() macro code in glibc_internal_abi.rs/unistd_abi.rs replaced by ~50 lines of marshalling over 3 pure-safe Rust formatters in core::{pwd, grp, pwd::shadow}. As a side benefit, putspent now correctly emits the -1 sentinel as empty (matching glibc) — the previous impl wrote the literal \"-1\".","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-piab","title":"syscall: sched_setaffinity invalid pid with valid mask should return ESRCH exactly","description":"Host glibc returns ESRCH for sched_setaffinity(-1, sizeof(cpu_set_t), &mask). Add focused ABI regression coverage so the invalid-pid contract is explicit.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:08:34.217116113Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-22T02:51:19.900178029Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T02:51:19.897958477Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-pjego","title":"PORT: strmode (BSD mode-bit-to-ls-style-string)","description":"BSD strmode(mode_t mode, char *buf) writes 11 ASCII chars + NUL into buf describing the file mode in ls -l format: file type (\"d\",\"l\",\"-\",\"c\",\"b\",\"p\",\"s\",\"w\",\"D\"), then 9 permission chars (rwx triples for owner/group/other) with setuid/setgid/sticky bit overlays (\"s\",\"S\",\"t\",\"T\"). Used by ls(1) implementations and any tool that wants to render mode bits human-readably. Currently missing from frankenlibc-abi/string_abi.rs. Ship as: pure-safe core::stat::strmode helper that returns a [u8; 11] (no NUL — caller writes the trailing NUL into a 12-byte buffer per BSD spec) + abi shim that copies the 11 bytes + NUL into the caller buffer.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T15:04:41.028852041Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T15:09:39.327642794Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T15:09:39.325721700Z","close_reason":"shipped: core::stat::strmode_bytes + string_abi::strmode; new core stat module; 28+8 tests; clippy-clean","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-pjnky","title":"PORT: 18 GLIBC_PRIVATE libnsl NIS+/yp internal helpers","description":"Add 18 GLIBC_PRIVATE libnsl internal NIS+/yp helper stubs to close the libnsl.so.1 last-mile gap. (1) __create_ib_request — NULL (allocator). (2) __do_niscall3 — NIS_NAMEUNREACHABLE=5 (no NIS+ server). (3) __follow_path — 0 (failure). (4) __free_fdresult — void no-op. (5) __nis_default_access/group/owner/ttl — return defaults: access=0, group/owner empty NULL strings, ttl=0. (6) __nis_finddirectory — NIS_NOTFOUND=1. (7) __nis_hash — return 0 (compute on empty input). (8) __nisbind_connect/create/destroy/next — -1/NULL/void/-1. (9) __prepare_niscall — NIS_NAMEUNREACHABLE=5. (10) __yp_check — 0 (no YP configured). (11) _xdr_ib_request / _xdr_nis_result — XDR encoders; return XDR_TRUE for empty data flow.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T21:34:59.283038994Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T21:34:59.283038994Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-pm-1","title":"PORT: proc_maps sub-bead 1 — core::proc_maps module","description":"Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/proc_maps/mod.rs with MapsEntry { start: usize, end: usize, perms: &str, offset: u64, dev: &str, inode: u64, path: Option<&str> }; parse_maps_line(line: &str) -> Option<MapsEntry>; parse_maps_range(line: &str) -> Option<(usize, usize)> as a thin shortcut over the start-end portion of the first whitespace-separated field. Tests cover: typical mapped library line with path, anonymous mapping (no path), VDSO/heap/stack named regions, malformed range fields, lines with extra trailing whitespace, hex parsing of large addresses (i.e., 64-bit), permission string variants (r--p, rw-p, r-xp, ---p).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/proc_maps/mod.rs with: MapsEntry<a> { start, end, perms, offset, dev, inode, path } as a borrowed view of one /proc/<pid>/maps line; parse_maps_line(line) -> Option<MapsEntry> handling typical mapped-library lines, anonymous mappings, pseudo-named regions ([stack]/[heap]/[vdso]/[vvar]), high 64-bit kernel addresses, all permission-string variants, EOL stripping, and rejecting truncated/malformed/extra-token lines; parse_maps_range(line) shortcut for callers that only need the start-end pair. 20 unit tests (13 parse_maps_line + 7 parse_maps_range) cover all the above cases plus a property test that range matches start/end of full parse.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-pm-2","title":"PORT: proc_maps sub-bead 2 — rewire abi callers","description":"Replace inline parse_maps_line in host_resolve.rs with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then apply the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. Replace pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range with a call to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_range. Verify both abi tests still pass.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"host_resolve.rs::parse_maps_line shrinks from ~25 to ~16 lines: it now delegates to core::proc_maps::parse_maps_line, then applies the libc.so + r--p + offset==0 filter on the returned MapsEntry. pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range becomes a 1-line forwarder. Both abi callers retain their specific filtering / output-shape logic at the boundary. 173/173 abi lib tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-pm-epic","title":"PORT: /proc/self/maps line parser to core::proc_maps","description":"Two abi files duplicate /proc/self/maps line parsing: host_resolve.rs::parse_maps_line (~25 lines, full parse with libc.so + perms + offset filters) and pthread_abi.rs::parse_maps_range (~7 lines, just the start-end address pair). Lift both into core::proc_maps with a shared MapsEntry struct + parse_maps_line, then rewire each abi caller to apply its specific filter on the borrowed result.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:05:20.017352Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:07:17.699830Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~32 lines of duplicated /proc/self/maps parsing across two abi files (host_resolve.rs + pthread_abi.rs) replaced by a single ~95-line core::proc_maps module with 20 isolation-tested cases. The full MapsEntry view is now reachable from any other caller that wants address/perms/offset/dev/inode/path beyond just the start-end range.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
