+{"id":"bd-v7fi8","title":"PORT: 25 libuuid functions (RFC 4122/v1/v3/v4/v5/v6/v7 UUID handling)","description":"Add 25 libuuid functions to close the libuuid.so.1 surface gap (DCE 1.1 / RFC 4122 / draft-ietf-uuidrev-rfc4122bis UUID handling). UUIDs are 16-byte structs; the API is pure-safe except for time/RNG entries which use getrandom + gettimeofday. (1) uuid_clear/uuid_copy/uuid_compare/uuid_is_null/uuid_variant/uuid_type — pure byte ops. (2) uuid_parse/uuid_parse_range/uuid_unparse{,_lower,_upper}/uuid_get_template — text<->bytes. (3) uuid_generate{,_random} — v4 from getrandom. (4) uuid_generate_time{,_safe,_cont,_v6,_v7} — v1/v6/v7 from gettimeofday + getrandom (RFC 4122 §4.5 random node-id). (5) uuid_generate_md5/uuid_generate_sha1 — v3/v5 namespace UUIDs via md-5 / sha2 crates. (6) uuid_time/uuid_time64 — extract v1 timestamp. (7) __uuid_generate_random/__uuid_generate_time/__uuid_generate_time_cont — internal-namespace aliases.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T21:25:59.184943738Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T21:32:55.570284203Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T21:32:55.568099726Z","close_reason":"withdrawn: project hooks gate libuuid out of scope (libuuid is util-linux's separate libuuid.so.1, not part of glibc's libc.so.6 — frankenlibc-abi only promises the libc surface). Keeping uuid_abi out of the crate per the explicit policy comment auto-injected on the test file.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
