 {"id":"bd-v9bcs","title":"PORT: 14 NIS / yp_* fail-safe libnsl stubs","description":"Add 14 fail-safe NIS / yp_* stubs (libnsl parity). NIS (Yellow Pages) is dead infrastructure; modern Linux systems do not run ypbind. These wrappers exist so binaries that statically reference yp_* through libc do not fail at link time, and graceful YPERR_NODOM (= 12, local NIS domain not set) is returned at runtime. (1) yp_get_default_domain(**outdomain): write NULL, return YPERR_NODOM. (2) yp_bind(*dom): return YPERR_DOMAIN. (3) yp_unbind(*dom): no-op. (4) yp_match / yp_first / yp_next / yp_all / yp_master / yp_order / yp_maplist / yp_update: zero out outputs, return YPERR_DOMAIN. (5) yperr_string(err) and ypbinderr_string(err): return static \"(no such NIS error)\" or known descriptions. (6) ypprot_err(code): convert ypbind protocol error code to YPERR_* (we just return YPERR_YPBIND).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T18:14:53.690149774Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T18:19:47.510011184Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T18:19:47.507760451Z","close_reason":"shipped: 14 NIS yp_* + yperr_string + ypbinderr_string + ypprot_err fail-safe stubs + 14 abi tests covering YPERR_* codes and output-zeroing semantics","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-vcma4","title":"PORT: warnc + vwarnc + errc + verrc (BSD err.h explicit-code variants)","description":"BSD/NetBSD <err.h> extensions warnc(code, fmt, ...), vwarnc(code, fmt, ap), errc(eval, code, fmt, ...), verrc(eval, code, fmt, ap) take an explicit errno code instead of consulting the global *__errno_location(). Useful when the caller has already preserved errno or wants to report a different code than the one currently set. Currently err_abi.rs ships warn/vwarn/warnx/vwarnx/err/verr/errx/verrx but is missing the explicit-code variants. Implement as 4 thin shims that call write_err_message with an overridden errno (refactor saved_errno injection) — no new core module needed since byte-level format_err_message in core already accepts the errno-text as a parameter.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:57:23.849761607Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T15:00:22.298852360Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T15:00:22.296941903Z","close_reason":"shipped: warnc/vwarnc/errc/verrc in err_abi.rs via shared write_err_message_with_code helper; 12 integration tests; clippy-clean","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

@@ -11351,3 +11351,156 @@ fn nss_systemd_block_is_per_thread() {
